    {
      "id": "description",
      "title": "Description",
      "body": "One of Sweden's premiere trad-crags. Classic crack and face climbing on fine-grained granite of extraordinary quality. There are a few bolted routes but the local climbing club and the Scandinavian climbing communities wishes no new bolts at Häller.\n\nPlease follow Bohusläns Klätterklubb's policy on staying bolt free in the future."
    },
    {
      "id": "directions",
      "title": "Directions",
      "body": "From E6 take road 162 towards Lysekil. Häller can be seen from the road a few kilometres after passing Hallinden. Follow signs towards Bro kyrka. Don't follow the old sign pointing to 'Häller', instead take Vrångebäcksvägen 100 m further south. Drive a kilometre on Vrångeväcksvägen then drive up to the farm just beneath the cliff. Pay 20 SKR for parking. If the parkinglot is full, consider going somewhere else, or park down at the main road.\n\nPlease read the access notes above.",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "kind": "paragraph",
          "text": "From E6 take road 162 towards Lysekil. Häller can be seen from the road a few kilometres after passing Hallinden. Follow signs towards Bro kyrka. Don't follow the old sign pointing to 'Häller', instead take Vrångebäcksvägen 100 m further south. Drive a kilometre on Vrångeväcksvägen then drive up to the farm just beneath the cliff. Pay 20 SKR for parking. If the parkinglot is full, consider going somewhere else, or park down at the main road."
        },
        {
          "kind": "heading",
          "text": "Please read the access notes above."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "season",
      "title": "Season",
      "body": "March--November."
    },
    {
      "id": "nuts-and-bolts",
      "title": "Nuts and Bolts",
      "body": "Most routes are well protected by a standard trad rack. If the grade is followed by a ”R”, the route is somewhat risky, if the grade is followed by an \"X\" a fall from the hard part of the route may very well be terminal.\n\nSome X-rated routes are protected by aid gear."
    }
  ],
