  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "49 documented routes and problems.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:haller"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "introduktion": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Introduction",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          }
        },
        "karaktar": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Character",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Classic crack and face climbing. Häller is covered by Bohuslän Climbing Club’s bolting policy and is to remain bolt-free in future.\n\nRoutes at this crag may carry the additional ratings R and X. R stands for “runout” and indicates a risk of long falls. R/X falls between R and X and indicates a risk of serious injury even when the available protection has been used. X indicates a risk of extremely long falls, where falling in the wrong place could be fatal.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          }
        },
        "access": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          }
        },
        "viktig-uppdatering-maj-2009": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Important Update, May 2009",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Serious breaches of access agreements with landowners; see http://www.klatterforbundet.se/nyheter.php?id=188. Be extremely careful to show consideration for landowners.\n\nParking is the main access issue at Häller. Take great care not to park where your car will obstruct the farmer’s work. Park in the small designated car park next to his house and pay the SEK 20 fee. If the car park is full, park elsewhere—not in his farmyard or on the dirt road leading up to the farm.\n\nThere have been reports of nesting kestrels at Häller, mainly on the ledge above the first pitch of “Tor Line” and the ledge above “Tratten”. Act accordingly: do not climb near these ledges in spring, from March to June. Note that some sectors of the crag may be completely closed in spring due to nesting birds.\n\nAll the usual access considerations apply at Häller, so keep a low profile. Remember that we are climbing on someone else’s property and behave accordingly. If you have to go, bury it deeply or wait until later. Leave no trace! If the crag looks crowded, go somewhere else for a couple of hours—there is plenty to choose from!",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:haller"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
          "title": {
